He gave His life; what more could He give?

00:51:16.730 --> 00:51:18.622
Oh, how He loves you.

00:51:18.622 --> 00:51:20.738
Oh, how He loves me.

00:51:20.738 --> 00:51:22.640
Oh, how He loves you and me.

00:51:31.120 --> 00:51:40.770
I wait on you.

00:51:40.770 --> 00:51:44.645
I'll have no other, for I'll love you only.

00:51:44.645 --> 00:51:47.620
I'll never forsake you or leave you alone.

00:51:47.620 --> 00:51:54.880
Here in your arms, I'll be at rest in the precious love you have for me.

00:52:05.663 --> 00:52:05.857
I love you.

00:52:05.857 --> 00:52:07.432
Oh, how I love you.

00:52:07.432 --> 00:52:10.312
I'll have no other, for I'll love you only.

00:52:10.312 --> 00:52:31.110
I'll never forsake you or leave you alone.

00:52:31.120 --> 00:52:32.302
Father, we worship you tonight.

00:52:32.302 --> 00:52:34.360
Thank you, Father, for the Holy Ghost river.

00:52:35.320 --> 00:52:37.592
We wait on you.

00:52:37.592 --> 00:52:39.760
We're never in a hurry.

00:52:50.800 --> 00:52:50.910
We're never rude when we come into your throne room and barge right in there and say, 'We demand, we want to hear, we want to see,' but Father, we come politely.

00:52:50.910 --> 00:52:59.145
Even if we come boldly, we come politely and we say, 'Lord, what is it that we could do for you tonight?

00:52:59.145 --> 00:53:15.465
' Not what we think or what we want to hear, but Father, everything that you want us to hear and for us to draw near—to draw near where you are, to come up higher with the fire and sit at your throne.

00:53:15.465 --> 00:53:19.720
For you said you inhabit the praises of your people.

00:53:20.093 --> 00:53:24.320
And we thank you, Lord, that tonight we dedicate this time.

00:53:24.320 --> 00:53:32.130
We separate ourselves for you to flow through us, Holy Spirit, that we add our supply in this world.

00:53:34.570 --> 00:53:35.260
I believe in miracles; I've seen a soul set free.

00:53:35.260 --> 00:53:39.000
Miraculous, the changing one redeemed through Calvary.

